thread.title: Grain lower, livestock mixed

title: Grain lower, livestock mixed
text:
Thu, Jul 16, 2015, 3:28 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 6 hrs 32 mins Grain lower, livestock mixed Grain mixed on the CBOT, beef mixed, pork higher on the CME Associated Press – 2 hours 12 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were lower Wednesdday in early trading on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was 8 cents lower to $5.63 a bushel; September corn was 1.4 cents lower at $4.2660 a bushel; December oats were 1 cent lower at $2.74 bushel; while November soybeans was 12.60 cents lower at 10.1220 cents a bushel. 
Beef was mixed and pork mixed on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
August live cattle was .38 cent lower at $1.4678 a pound; August feeder cattle was .60 cent higher at $2.1490 a pound; August lean hogs lost .75 cent to $.7585 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook David Jones performing well for new owners AAP
